From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Entrpi <entrpi@proton.me>
Date: Wed, 10 Dec 2025 14:35:30 +0800
Subject: [PATCH] soc: cix: Add Sky1 SoC information driver

Add SoC information driver for CIX Sky1 that exposes chip and board
identification via the soc_device framework.

Information sources:
- SRAM region: Firmware versions (SE, PBL, ATF, PM, TEE, UEFI, EC, PD)
  and board ID (PCB SKU, PMIC, memory type, revision)
- NVMEM efuse: OPN (Ordering Part Number) with segment, model, roadmap,
  and silicon revision

Exposed via standard sysfs interface at /sys/devices/soc0/:
- family: "CIX Sky1"
- soc_id: Parsed OPN string (e.g., "P8180B11A0")
- revision: Silicon revision (A0/A1/B0/B1)
- firmware_version: All firmware component versions
- board_info: PCB SKU, PMIC type, memory configuration
- cix_opn_info: Full OPN identification string

Ported from vendor kernel with mainline improvements:
- Use soc_device framework with custom_attr_group
- devm_* APIs for resource management
- GENMASK_ULL/FIELD_GET for bit field extraction
- sysfs_emit() for attribute output
